ope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> Following <em>Spectre</em> , Scott has starred in the likes of <em>Fleabag</em> , <em>1917</em> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/black-mirror"><em>Black Mirror</em></a> , <em>His Dark Materials</em> and <em>Catherine Called Birdy</em> .</p><p> He next stars opposite Paul Mescal in <em>All Of Us Strangers</em> , a romance film from director Andrew Haigh ( <em>45 Years, Looking</em> ). Other cast members include Jamie Bell and Claire Foy.</p><p> <em>All Of Us Strangers</em> is scheduled to be released in UK cinemas on January 26, 2024.</p><p> Daniel Craig made his final bow as Bond in 2021&#39;s <em>No Time To Die</em> . Recently, producer Barbara Broccoli revealed that <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/james-bond-developing-new-film-3533212">work on the next outing is not in active development yet</a> .</p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/andrew-scott-doesnt-think-he-that-good-james-bond-movie-spectre-3537950">Andrew Scott doesn&#39;t think he was “that good” in James Bond movie &#39;Spectre&#39;</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
